CARMEN XIV. A.U.c. 729 or 730.

This ode has been animadverted upon pretty severely, and even rejected as spurious, because unequal to the occasion it was written for. It may not be one of Horace’s best· But it was evidently only a private affair. It was composed at the close of the Canta- brian war, A.U.c. 729, when Augustus' return was expected, or on his return the follow- ing year. He was detained by illness at Tarraco. Franke gives, firom Nox-isius, a fragment of an inscription which makes it appear probable that Augustus recovered his health and returned in the summer of 730, in which year C. Norbanus Flaccus was consul:
